This is the **backend** of my full-stack **Library Management System** project, built using **Node.js**, **Express.js**, and **MongoDB**.

---

##  Live API Base URL
https://backend-library-management-system.onrender.com

---

## âš™ Features

- User Authentication (JWT)
- Admin and User Roles
- Book Management (CRUD)
- Borrow/Return System
- Review System
- Weekly Statistics API
- Middleware & Error Handling

---

##  Folder Structure
/src
/config # DB connect and env config
/controllers # Backend and Database logic
/models # Mongoose schemas
/routers # Route definitions
/middlewares # Auth,Admin, Demo Admin and error handlers
/utils # Utility functions, bcryptjs, multer, jwts

---

##  Tech Stack

- Node.js
- Express.js
- MongoDB + Mongoose
- JSON Web Token (JWT)
- Render for deployment

---
##  Running Locally

bash
# Clone repo
git clone https://github.com/bishes7/backend-library-management-system.git

# Install dependencies
npm install

# Setup environment variables (Examples)
MONGO_URL=your-mongo-db-url
JWT_SECRET=your-secret

# Start the server
yarn dev

# API Testing
Use Postman or rest.http to test the following routes:

POST /register
POST /login
GET /books
POST /books
PUT /books/:id
DELETE /books/:id
etc...

